    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>First, using a menu to do this may be the wrong approach.  <code>JSpinner</code> seems more appropriate.  However, to do this with a <code>JMenuItem</code> you can subclass the <code>MenuItemUI</code> of the <code>LookAndFeel</code> you are using, and override the <code>doClick(...)</code> method so that <code>clearSelectionPath()</code> is not called, which closes the menu when the item is clicked.</p>\n\n<p>Example, if you are using the Motif <code>LookAndFeel</code> you can do this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>menuItem.setUI(new MotifMenuItemUI() {\n    @Override\n    protected void doClick(MenuSelectionManager msm) {\n        menuItem.doClick(0);\n    }\n});\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I haven't ever tried this myself but I think it will work.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 283267,
      "reputation" : 867,
      "user_id" : 580672,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ac25c651a212e455cc32be1522c42be6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Philippp",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/580672/philippp"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763064471,
    "creation_date" : 1763064471,
    "answer_id" : 79819383,
    "question_id" : 9198530,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have another idea: Use an empty <code>JMenu</code> instead of each <code>JMenuItem</code>. <code>JMenu</code>s do not cause the popup to close!</p>\n<p>Granted, they are not intended for assigning actions to them (at selection/mouse click), but it is possible to attach listeners that can handle the click. And in the listener you can then programmatically close or not close the popup (maybe depending on whether a modifier key like Ctrl was pressed during the click).</p>\n<p>The only thing I am not sure about is whether selecting the menu using the Enter key (as an alternative to the mouse click) would also work, you will probably need another listener.</p>\n"
  } ],
