  "title" : "How to prevent JMenuItem from closing Menu upon clicking the JMenuItem",
  "body" : "<p>How do I prevent a <code>JMenuItem</code> from closing the menu when the <code>JMenuItem</code> is clicked?</p>\n\n<p>The <code>JMenuItem</code> is enabled. </p>\n\n<p>So this is the scenario, I have 3 <code>JMenuItems</code>:</p>\n\n<p><code>JMenuItem: A, B, C</code>;</p>\n\n<p>C displays an integer <code>X</code>.</p>\n\n<p>A and B are used to increment or decrement <code>X</code> by a value of 1.\nIf A or B is clicked, the default nature is that the menu will close upon click.\nI want to be able to repeatedly click A or B and have the menu remain up, and perform the associated 'action' upon each click.</p>\n\n<p>Thanks! </p>\n"
}